@eps1lon Some people don't need the transition. The approach I have linked improves the performance when the modal is closed. **It skips the rendering of the whole Modal children**, depending on your app, it can be a large tree. It's not related to Suspense.

Now, if we stop supporting this approach, people can still get most of the rendering pruning by creating an intermediary component: https://material-ui.com/utils/modal/#performance.

